The U.S. Senate has approved ameasure that would allow an estimated 4,200 agricultural banksto write off loan losses over ten years.    The measure, offered by Sen. Alan Dixon (D-Ill.), wasattached to a bill to recapitalize the Federal Savings and LoanInsurance Corp that the Senate approved March 27.    Dixon's amendment would permit agricultural banks -- bankswith assets of 100 mln dlrs or less and at least 25 pct oftotal loans in farm loans -- to write down over ten yearsagricultural loan losses incurred between 1984 and 1992. Reuter&#3;